{"id":"282620711_Accurate_and_Efficient_Evaluation_of_Transition_Probabilities_at_Unavoided_Crossings_in_Ab_Initio_Multiple_Spawning","abstract":"Recently we introduced a norm-preserving wavefunction interpolation (NPI) method which allows the accurate and efficient integration of the time-dependent Schrödinger equation in regions of rapidly varying time-derivative coupling (TDC), e.g. near conical intersections (CIs) and effectively (N-1)-dimensional trivial unavoided crossings (TUCs). Herein we report the implementation of the NPI scheme into the ab initio multiple spawning (AIMS) method and investigate its behavior in two test systems: one which exhibits a CI and another which exhibits a TUC. In the CI case, AIMS–NPI predicts transfer probabilities that agree to within 0.6% of simulations based on the analytical evaluation of the nonadiabatic couplings, without the need for computationally expensive adaptive integration. In the TUC case, AIMS–NPI results in less than 0.08% error in the population transfer probability when a 0.12 fs time step is used, while simulations based on the analytical approach exhibit catastrophic errors for all finite time steps.","authors":["Garrett A. Meek","Benjamin G. Levine"],"meta":["June 2015Chemical Physics 460","DOI:10.1016/j.chemphys.2015.06.007"],"references":["269420982_Ab_Initio_Multiple_Cloning_Simulations_of_Pyrrole_Photodissociation_TKER_Spectra_and_Velocity_Map_Imaging","268207863_Semiclassical_Monte_Carlo_A_first_principles_approach_to_non-adiabatic_molecular_dynamics","264643949_Ab_initio_multiple_cloning_algorithm_for_quantum_nonadiabatic_molecular_dynamics","258007640_Time-dependent_approach_to_semiclassical_dynamics","253972669_Quantum_decoherence_in_mixed_quantum-classical_systems_Nonadiabatic_processes","253630292_Semiclassical-Limit_Molecular_Dynamics_on_Multiple_Electronic_Surfaces","234962603_Density-matrix_representation_of_nonadiabatic_couplings_in_time-dependent_density_functional_TDDFT_theories","234956817_D